[SN]TITLE[SN]
Tributes to father who died in Port Talbot car crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man who died in a car crash in Neath Port Talbot was a "fun-loving character who doted on his two children", his family have said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Andrew Lee Thomas James, 26, from Penrhiwfer, Rhondda Cynon Taff, died following the collision on Afan Way, Port Talbot, at 21:55 BST on Sunday.
Three others remain in hospital.
In a statement, his family said: "He had such a heart of gold. He would help anyone at any time. He loved life and definitely lived it to the full."
The tribute added: "Andrew was a fun-loving character. He was a loving son, step-son,  brother, uncle and grandson.
"His death has left such a massive void in all our lives that can never be filled. He will be missed by everyone who knew him."
South Wales Police said the investigation into the collision involving a silver Suzuki Ignis and a black Ford Focus is continuing.
